The paper focuses on policy search for robot navigation, which falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO). The use of Bayesian optimization and probabilistic surrogate models suggests a focus on artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The exploration of different optimization benchmarks and robot tasks suggests a focus on systems and control (cs.SY) and computer vision (cs.CV).
